condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :EEPCO additional event of suspension | Description :The Kenya Financing Agreement shall have failed to becomeeffective twenty-four (24) months after the Effective Date of the Ethiopia FA. | Due Date :06-Dec-2015

Finance Agreement :EEPCO disbursement condition | Description :No disbursements will be made under Category (1)(c) (works, goodsand non-consulting services) for the converter substation to be constructed in Ethiopia, until and unless EEPCo has adopted,consulted upon and disclosed the RAP for the converter substation as approved by the Association and the displaced persons havebeen compensated in accordance with the RAP. | Due Date :30-Sep-2015

Finance Agreement :EEPCO environment | Description :EEPCo shall take all measures required to ensure its Environmental MonitoringUnit is maintained throughout project implementation within its structure under terms of reference satisfactory to the Associationand with financial, technical and administrative resources adequate to enable it to carry out the ESIA, ESMP, RPF and the RAP in atimely and diligent manner. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :EEPCO financial viability | Description :Not later than May 15 of each year during project implementation,starting in calendar year 2013, the Recipient shall cause EEPCo to prepare and furnish to the Association, an annual progressreport on the implementation and update of the Financial Viability Plan, including measures recommended to ensure the continuedfinancial viability of EEPCo. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :EEPCO financial viability | Description :The Recipient shall cause EEPCo to prepare and furnish to theAssociation a plan designed to ensure its financial viability in the next three (3) years following the Association's approval ofthe Project (“Financial Viability Plan”). | Due Date :14-Jun-2013

Finance Agreement :EEPCO resettlement | Description :EEPCo shall: (i) prepare and carry out the Resettlement Action Plan asdesigned and stipulated in the Resettlement Policy Framework; and (ii) implement the provisions of the Environmental and SocialImpact Assessment and the Environmental and Social Management Plan (ESMP), all in a manner satisfactory to the Association. |Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :GoK - AFD loan effectiveness (4.02 of amendment) | Description :The Co-financing Deadline for the effectivenessof the Co-financing Agreement between the GoK and AFD is 12 months after the Effective Date. | Due Date :24-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :KETRACO additional event of suspension | Description :Kenya shall have failed to submit to the Association, notlater than twelve (12) months after the Effective Date, the Wheeling Agreement between KPLC and KETRACO as approved by the KenyaEnergy Regulatory Commission. | Due Date :24-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement :KETRACO disbursement condition | Description :No disbursement will be made under Category (1)(c) (works, goodsand non-consulting services) for the converter substation to be constructed in Kenya, until and unless all conditions ofdisbursement to finance the construction of the converter substation in Ethiopia (Part A.2 of the Project stipulated in theEthiopia Financing Agreement) have been met. | Due Date :30-Sep-2015

Finance Agreement :KETRACO resettlement | Description :KETRACO shall take all measures required on its behalf to establish byDecember 31, 2013, one or more County Resettlement Action Plan Committees in each of the Isiolo, Laikipia, Marsabit, Nakuru,Nyandarua and Samburu counties to be responsible for the day-to-dayimplementation of the RAP, all under terms of reference and withstaff with experience and qualifications satisfactory to IDA. | Due Date :31-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :KETRACO resettlement | Description :KETRACO shall, by December 31, 2013, employ a firm or group of independentpersons to serve as an independent resettlement evaluation panel charged with the task of: (i) monitoring the progress in theimplementation of the RAP, incl. verifying reports and making site visits to obtain information from the project affectedpersons;and (ii) conducting semi-annual audits and a close-down audit. | Due Date :31-Dec-2013
